Um...<br>
the Anne series by LM Montgomery<br>
Little Women, by Louisa May Alcott<br>
Emma, by Jane Austen<br>
all the rest of Jane Austen's books!<br>
Mill on the Floss, by George Elliot<br>
The Scarlet Letter, by Nathaniel Hawthorne<br>
the Little House books, by Laura Ingalls Wilder<br>
-----<br>
Three Musketeers, by Alexandre Dumas<br>
Treasure Island, by RL Stevenson<br>
War and Peace, by Tolstoy<br>
Jane Eyre, by one of those Bronte sisters<br>
<br>
This is a start. There are all kinds of different books here, and I wouldn't suggest starting with War &amp; Peace, no matter how much I love it.<br>
